<number box="[378,437,506,532]" pageId="2" pageNumber="359" value="1913.0">1913</number>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,577,745]" pageId="2" pageNumber="359">
Species of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[412,515,578,601]" class="Malacostraca" family="Atyidae" genus="Micratya" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="359" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[412,515,578,601]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="359">Micratya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
show a reduced branchial formula (
<figureCitation box="[956,1031,577,601]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1075,1098]" captionText="FIGURE 2. Branchial formula in the genus Micratya" pageId="2" pageNumber="359">
Fig. 
<number box="[1015,1031,577,601]" pageId="2" pageNumber="359" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
), lacking pleurobranchies on fifth pereiopod. There are also no epipods on the fourth pereiopod. For these characters 
<taxonomicName box="[1080,1183,614,637]" class="Malacostraca" family="Atyidae" genus="Micratya" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="359" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1080,1183,614,637]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="359">Micratya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[151,302,649,673]" class="Malacostraca" family="Atyidae" genus="Halocaridina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="359" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,302,649,673]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="359">Halocaridina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Hawaii, but 
<taxonomicName box="[508,610,650,673]" class="Malacostraca" family="Atyidae" genus="Micratya" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="359" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[508,610,650,673]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="359">Micratya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has one well developed and one reduced arthrobranch at third maxilliped and podobranchies on second maxilliped. This character combination resembles the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1172,1344,685,709]" class="Malacostraca" family="Atyidae" genus="Limnocaridella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="359" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1172,1344,685,709]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="359">Limnocaridella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the latter lacks podobranchies at second maxilliped.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
